int func(void);		// use void if there is no parameter is passing through the function

int *i, *j			// use place the * close to the variable name not pointer type

* typedef statement in header file to declare the type for other parts of the program

* mystruct_val_type becomes the struct type

* struct mystruct_struct becomes mystruct_type

lib.c lib.h files should be in snake

use underscore conventions

int func() {
	// declare functions like this	
}

if (soemthing) {
	if (something) {
		// always put braces even if it is single line
	}
}

